column1: SEC-HS Jamboree #2 (Red) Mens 5000 Meters Reserve Boys

The Skyline boys JV cross country team hit the course at the SEC-HS Jamboree #2, racing hard and leaving nothing behind. While the varsity teams grabbed the headlines, the JV squad quietly showed theyâ€™re more than ready to make their own mark.

Leading the way was sophomore Enshu Kuan, who finished with a time of 18:29.50. Hot on his heels, freshman Dylan Hanley clocked in at 18:33.30, with solid performances from Zeke Lafferty (18:20.60), Hudson McCleskey (18:42.30), and Cooper Ankeney (18:45.10).
